<TEXT>
<P>
 Miscellany  
</P>
<P>
 The Big West Conference will consider expanding beyond its current eight 
member schools, Commissioner Dennis Farrell said Sunday after a special meeting 
of athletic directors and chief executive officers. 
</P>
<P>
 "We will be looking into expansion, but we'll only expand if we feel it will 
strengthen the conference," Farrell said. " . . . We'll be contacting some 
schools to see what their interest might be in our conference." 
</P>
<P>
 Farrell declined to identify the schools the conference will approach, but it 
is believed that Cal State Northridge is one. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge has applied for membership into the Big West the past three years. 
Further discussion about expansion is expected to take place when conference 
officials meet again in two weeks. 
</P>
