<P>
 Mike Cofer, an NFL free-agent kicker, won his first stock car racing event, 
taking the Plummer Pontiac 100 at Stockton 99 Speedway. 
</P>
<P>
 Driving a Chevrolet Lumina, Cofer led wire to wire Saturday night and won 
$4,425 in his sixth start on the NASCAR Featherlite Southwest Tour. 
</P>
<P>
 He beat Steve Johnson, in a Pontiac TransAm, by two seconds. Pro Basketball  
</P>
<P>
 New York City police plan to question Derrick Coleman and Jason Williams of 
the New Jersey Nets about a late-night street brawl in which three teen-agers 
were injured. 
</P>
<P>
 The three teens alleged that Coleman and Williams were among a group of men 
who fought with them outside a bar in the Chelsea section of Manhattan at 4 
a.m. on Saturday, said Officer Scott Bloch, a police spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the teen-agers received six stitches for a head wound, another was 
punched in the arm and the third sustained a hand injury, a police spokesman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 John Mertz, director of public relations for the New Jersey Nets, said he and 
the two players would have no comment. 
</P>
