</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
77 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA VOICES / A FORUM FOR COMMUNITY ISSUES: GRIPE; 'EVERY 
BUILDING SHOULD HAVE A STREET NUMBER' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MILTON L. TAUBKIN 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
<P>
 I wonder how many people are frustrated as much as I am with trying to find a 
home or business by its street number.I am amazed that it is possible to go 
down a whole street in some areas without a building having a number on it. 
</P>
<P>
 I would like others to also lend their voices by insisting that every building 
have a street number clearly marked on it for identification. There ought to be 
a "law" to that effect. No? 
</P>
