<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BUENA PARK; COUNCIL TO COMMENT ON FIRE SERVICES PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It will be the turn of city officials and staff tonight to comment on a 
proposal for Buena Park to contract fire services with Orange County Fire 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The council has already had two public information meetings, during which 
residents have asked hundreds of question about the proposal, but today's 5 
p.m. session will focus on comments from city staff and council members. 
</P>
<P>
 The public will also be able to address the council. 
</P>
<P>
 Another public hearing and the council decision is expected at the May 16 
meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the county's contract proposal, one of the city's four engine companies 
would be eliminated. 
</P>
<P>
 The county is offering two options. Under one, the city would pay $4.7 million 
a year and would add a fourth firefighter to one firetruck, which has aerial 
and rescue equipment. 
</P>
<P>
 The second option would cost $4.4 million and keep the truck company at its 
current level of three firefighters. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will be at the council's chambers, 6650 Beach Blvd. For more 
information, call (714) 562-3500. 
</P>
</TEXT>
