<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; ALTERNATE NAMED TO DISCIPLINARY PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has appointed an alternate member to an advisory citizen 
panel that reviews disciplinary actions against employees. 
</P>
<P>
 John McShane was selected last week to fill in for Wanda Bell, who will not be 
able to attend Merit System Commission hearings this month.The other commission 
members are Anji D. Clemens and Randy Hill. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission members are chosen from among educators, the clergy and the 
public. Bell, appointed recently following the resignation of Earl French, is 
the public representative. Clemens, an assistant principal at Westminster High 
School, represents educators, and Hill, pastor of the First Nazarene Church, 
represents the clergy. 
</P>
<P>
 The Merit System Commission reviews disciplinary actions against employees and 
may conduct public hearings on appeals from suspension, dismissal or demotion. 
They submit their findings to the council, which has the final say on 
employee-related matters, short of an appeal to the courts. BERT ELJERA 
