<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRUCK THEFT SUSPECT DIES IN COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A truck theft suspect who led police on a chase that began in Yorba Linda and 
passed through six cities was killed Sunday when the stolen pickup he was 
driving crashed in Commerce, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities declined to identify the suspect, who died shortly after the 
pickup collided with a van and another vehicle at the intersection of 
Washington Boulevard and Garfield Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Three passengers in the van were injured. Authorities said they were 
hospitalized but their injuries were not life-threatening. The driver of the 
car was not injured. 
</P>
<P>
 The chase began about 8:25 a.m. when Brea police spotted a red Mazda pickup 
truck that had been reported stolen to the Orange County Sheriff's Department 
three days earlier, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers tried to stop the vehicle in the 4700 block of Green Crest Drive in 
Yorba Linda but the driver sped away, leading police on a chase through Yorba 
Linda, Brea, La Habra, Montebello, Whittier and Commerce. 
</P>
<P>
 The pursuit covered about 25 miles and reached speeds up to 90 m.p.h., police 
said. 
</P>
