<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; BOARD APPROVES NEW SCHOOL CHOICE POLICY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura Unified School District board has approved a new school choice 
policy that will allow parents to send their children to any public schools in 
the district that have room. 
</P>
<P>
 Beginning this spring, parents will be able to apply to transfer their 
children from their neighborhood schools to any others in the district, if 
space is available. 
</P>
<P>
 Before the change in policy, parents had to show a compelling reason for a 
transfer, such as wanting their child to take a course not available at their 
neighborhood school. 
</P>
<P>
 But under the new rules, parents will be able to request a switch to another 
school without having to give a reason for the move. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications for transfers will be available at all district schools. MAIA 
DAVIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
