<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA PAULA; MOTORCYCLIST, 19, HURT IN ACCIDENT DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 19-year-old Santa Paula man died early Sunday, more than a week after 
suffering major head injuries in a motorcycle accident at a Santa Paula store 
parking lot, Deputy Coroner Craig Stevens said. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Lister succumbed to blunt head injuries at 3:10 a.m., Stevens said. 
</P>
<P>
 Lister was discovered after his accident by Santa Paula police about 6:30 p.m. 
April 22 in the rear of the K mart parking lot near Faulkner Road. 
</P>
<P>
 There were no witnesses, but police said Lister was probably driving through 
the parking lot when he lost control of the motorcycle, fell to the pavement 
and hit a curb. 
</P>
<P>
 Lister, who was not wearing a helmet, was transported to Santa Paula Memorial 
Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 He was later transferred to Ventura County Medical Center, where he had been 
listed in critical condition in the intensive care unit for 10 days, a nursing 
supervisor said. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
