<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: OPEN HOUSE FOR TEACHERS PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOANNA M. MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Teachers preparing for administrative roles or looking to further their 
careers are invited to an open house Wednesday at Cal State Northridge's 
Ventura campus. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ventura campus offers both a master's degree in educational administration 
and a preliminary administrative credential, which are useful to those 
preparing to become principals or assume other administrative roles. 
</P>
<P>
 "I have encouraged this degree for women and minorities who want to advance to 
administrative roles," said Joyce M. Kennedy, director of the Ventura campus. 
</P>
<P>
 "Very often in the past, women were locked in the teaching role, and men 
tended to get promoted to administrative positions. This is a chance to advance 
not only into administrative roles but in their teaching careers as well." 
</P>
<P>
 Among the courses offered in the curriculum are those in organizational 
administration, curriculum development, school and community relations, and 
California school law. 
</P>
<P>
 Faculty members from the department will be on hand to answer questions. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call the campus at 654-4575. JOANNA M. MILLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
